article.headline: Toledo 69, Northern Illinois 61
article.story: TOLEDO, Ohio (AP) -- Keith Triplett scored 11 of his 15 points during a 25-0 second-half run to lead Toledo to a 69-61 victory over Northern Illinois on Wednesday night. The Rockets (16-5, 10-3 Mid-American Conference) trailed 44-27 after Perry Smith, who led Northern Illinois (7-15, 2-10) with 14 points, hit a 3-pointer with 16:42 remaining. Toledo then reeled off the next 25 points, holding the Huskies scoreless for more than 7 minutes. Triplett hit two 3-pointers in the surge, while A.J. Shellabarger had five points off the bench. Justin Ingram also hit a 3-pointer. Northern Illinois drew as close as 59-55 with 5 minutes left, but Sammy Villegas, who scored 11 points for the Rockets, countered with a 3-pointer and the lead never fell below seven points again. Florentino Valencia added 11 points for Toledo. Walter Thompson scored 13 points and Rome Sanders had 12 for Northern Illinois, which hit just 27 percent of its shots from the field in the second half compared to the Rockets' 55 percent.
